
## Encrypt Example: PayWithMyBank

> PayWithMyBank example: 

```xml
<Encrypt>
  <shopLogin>90000001</shopLogin>
  <uicCode>242</uicCode><!-- Euro -->
  <amount>0.10</amount>
  <shopTransactionId>MYSHOP_001</shopTransactionId>
  <paymentTypes>
    <paymentType>PWMYBANK</paymentType>
  </paymentTypes>
  <!-- optional -->
  <OrderDetails>
    <CustomerDetail>
      <PrimaryEmail>kesuke.myagi@karatekid.com</PrimaryEmail>
      <FirstName>Kesuke</FirstName>
    </CustomerDetail>
    <BillingAddress>
      <CountryCode>US</CountryCode>
    </BillingAddress>
  </OrderDetails>
</Encrypt>
```

You must use `PWMYBANK` as `paymentType`.

PayWithMyBank requires two mandatory parameters: 

| Parameter | Description | 
| --------- | ----------- | 
| `PrimaryEmail` | _required_. the email address. Found in `OrderDetails` -> `CustomerDetail` |
| `FirstName` | _required_. the customer's name. Found in `OrderDetails` -> `CustomerDetail` |
| `CountryCode` | _optional_. Found in `OrderDetails` -> `BillingAddress`. With PayWithMyBank, this value must be `US`. | 

Click on [`OrderDetails`](#orderdetails) to know more about its structure.

